    <summary>An enhanced REPL for Common Lisp</summary>
    <description><![CDATA[ICL (Interactive Common Lisp) provides a modern, feature-rich REPL for Common Lisp with:

- Multi-line input with readline-style editing
- Persistent command history
- Tab completion for symbols and packages
- Extensible comma-prefixed command system (,help, ,quit, ,info, etc.)
- Support for multiple Lisp implementations via Slynk
- Documentation lookup, object inspection, and tracing

## Requirements

ICL requires a Common Lisp implementation to be installed. Supported implementations:
- SBCL (recommended) - install with: `choco install sbcl`
- CCL (Clozure CL)
- ECL (Embeddable Common Lisp)
- CLISP
- ABCL (Armed Bear Common Lisp)

## Usage

After installation, run `icl` from the command line:

```
icl                    # Start REPL (auto-detects Lisp)
icl --lisp sbcl        # Use specific Lisp implementation
icl -e "(+ 1 2)"       # Evaluate expression and exit
icl --help             # Show all options
```

## REPL Commands

Type `,help` in the REPL to see available commands.
